==English==
===Etymology===
From Old English ''[[ajoinen]]'', from Old French ''[[ajoindre]]'', (compare French ''[[adjoindre]]''), from Latin ''[[adjungere]]'', formed from ''[[ad-]]'' + ''[[jungere]]'' "to join".

===Pronunciation===
* ''US:''
** {{IPA|/ʌˈʤɔɪn.ɪŋ/}}

===Adjective===
'''adjoining'''
# Being in [[contact]] at some point or line; joining to; contiguous; bordering: ''an adjoining room''.

====Synonyms====
*[[adjacent]]
*[[bordering]]

====Antonyms====
*[[separated]]

===Verb===
'''adjoining'''
# Present participle of ''to [[adjoin]]''.

